name: Stellarnova Bonds
desc:
You can only activate a card with this card's name once per turn.
①：Activate one of the following effects, but you cannot Special Summon monsters from the Extra Deck for the rest of the turn, except Xyz Monsters.
● Discard 1 card, and if you do, Special Summon 1 "Tellarknight" or "Constellar" monster from your Deck with a different Type than the monsters you control.
● Target face-up monsters on your opponent's field up to the number of "Tellarknight" or "Constellar" monsters you control; negate those monsters' effects until the end of the turn.

name: Dark Staring at the Blue Sky
desc:
You can only use the ①, ② and ③ effects of this card's name once per turn.
①：If a monster(s) is Special Summoned from the Deck and/or Extra Deck by an opponent's activated monster effect while this card is in your GY: You can Special Summon it.
②：When a monster effect is activated that includes Special Summoning a monster(s) (Quick Effect): You can banish 1 card from your hand or field; negate that effect, and if you do, destroy that card.
③：During the End Phase, if this card is currently banished, and was banished this turn: You can return 1 of your other banished monsters to the GY.

name: First Penguin
desc:
You can only use the ② effect of this card's name once per turn.
①：If you control no face-up monsters, you can Special Summon this card (from your hand), and if you do, it is treated as a Tuner.
②：You can discard 1 card and reveal 1 WATER Synchro Monster in your Extra Deck; add 1 WATER monster with the same Type as the revealed monster, but 1 Level lower, from your Deck to your hand, then you can change this card to face-down Defense Position, also you cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn, except WATER monsters.

name: Forbidden Ritual Art
desc:
Note: Temporarily unavailable

You can only use the ① and ② effects of this card's name each once per turn.
①：Ritual Summon 1 Ritual Monster from your GY, by banishing other monsters from your GY whose total Levels exactly equal its Level, but destroy it during the End Phase.
②：You can banish this card from your GY; once this turn, when you Ritual Summon with a card effect that requires monsters, you can also banish Ritual Monsters from your GY as monsters used for the Ritual Summon.

name: Tip of the Tongue Reduction
desc:
①：When your opponent activates a card or effect by declaring exactly 1 card name: Negate that effect, then you can add 1 card with that name from your Deck to your hand.
②：If this Set card in its owner's control is destroyed by an opponent's card effect: You can target 1 face-up monster they control; it loses 500 ATK.

name: Shichigosan Shugo
desc:
①：Special Summon 1 Level/Rank 1 monster from either GY, and if you do, equip this card to it.
②：Once per turn, during the End Phase: Increase the equipped monster's Level/Rank by 1.
③：Apply these effects based on the equipped monster's Level/Rank.
● 3+: It gains ATK equal to its original ATK.
● 5+: It is unaffected by your opponent's activated effects.
④：Once per turn, during your Standby Phase, if the equipped monster's Level/Rank is 7 or higher: Send all cards on the field to the GY.

name: Reeshaddoll Wendiculhu
desc:
1 "Shaddoll" monster + 1 WIND monster
Must first be Fusion Summoned. You can only use the ① effect of this card's name once per turn.
①：(Quick Effect): You can change any number of Set monsters to face-up Defense Position, then you can change other face-up monsters on the field to face-down Defense Position up to the number of Flip monsters flipped face-up.
②：If this card is sent to the GY: You can target 1 "Shaddoll" card in your GY; add it to your hand.

name: Fallen of the White Dragon
desc:
This card is always treated as "Fallen of Albaz". You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：If this card is in your hand: You can send 1 monster that mentions "Fallen of Albaz" from your Extra Deck to the GY; Special Summon this card, also you cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn, except Level 8 Fusion and Synchro Monsters.
②：If this card is Normal or Special Summoned: You can Special Summon 1 "Ecclesia" monster from your hand, Deck, or GY.

name: Ecclesia of the Black Dragon
desc:
1 Tuner + 1+ non-Tuner monsters
You can only use the ① and ② effects of this card's name once per turn.
①：During the Main Phase (Quick Effect): You can banish this card (until the End Phase), and if you do, Special Summon 1 "Fallen of Albaz" or 1 Level 4 or lower monster that mentions it from your Deck or GY.
②：If this card is in your GY: You can target 1 Level 8 Fusion Monster in your GY or banishment and 1 card on the field; shuffle both and this card into the Deck.

name: Rescue-ACE Quick Attacker
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effects of this card's name each once per turn.
①：You can shuffle 1 other "Rescue-ACE" card from your hand or face-up field into the Deck; Special Summon this card from your hand.
②：You can Tribute this card; you cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn, except FIRE monsters, also add 1 "Rescue-ACE" monster from your Deck to your hand, then, if only your opponent controls a monster, you can Special Summon the added monster.

name: Rescue-ACE Arbitrator
desc:
2+ FIRE monsters
You can only Special Summon "Rescue-ACE Arbitrator" once per turn, and you can only use its ② effect twice per turn.
①：If this card is Link Summoned: You can add 1 "Rescue-ACE Hydrant" or "Rescue-ACE HQ" from your Deck or GY to your hand.
②：If you activate a "Rescue-ACE" Quick-Play Spell or Normal Trap: You can target 1 card on your opponent's field; destroy that target.

name: Exosister Karmael
desc:
2 Level 4 "Exosister" monsters
You can only use the ① and ② effects of this card's name once per turn.
①：If this card is Xyz Summoned: You can activate this effect; during the End Phase of this turn, Set 1 "Exosister" Spell/Trap from your Deck, GY, or banishment.
②：When your opponent activates a Normal Spell/Trap Card or a monster effect (Quick Effect): You can detach all material from this card, and if you do, that effect becomes "Add 1 card from your opponent's GY to their hand".

name: Exosister Bat Mater
desc:
You can only use the ①, ② and ③ effects of this card's name once per turn.
①：When this card resolves, add 2 "Exosister" monsters from your Deck to your hand, then discard 1 card.
②：You can target 1 face-up monster you control; immediately after this effect resolves, Normal Summon 1 "Exosister" monster mentioned on it.
③：If a monster(s) is sent to your opponent's GY (even during the Damage Step): You can make your opponent banish 1 of them.

name: Artmage Non Finito
desc:
2 "Artmage" monsters
Must be either Fusion Summoned, or Special Summoned (from your Extra Deck) by discarding 1 Spell/Trap and Tributing 1 Level 7 or higher "Artmage" monster from your hand or field. You can only Special Summon "Artmage Non Finito" once per turn this way, no matter which method you use.
①：If this card is Special Summoned: You can Set 1 "Artmage" Spell/Trap from your Deck.
②：Once per opponent's turn (Quick Effect): You can Fusion Summon 1 Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck using monsters you control.

name: Sheena the Twin Storm Deities of Divine Thunder
desc:
You can only use the ① effect of this card's name once per turn.
①：When your opponent activates a card or effect while you control a WIND monster (Quick Effect): You can Special Summon this card from your hand, then apply this effect based on that card effect's type.
● Monster: Return all face-up monsters on the field to the hand, except "Sheena the Twin Storm Deities of Divine Thunder".
● Spell/Trap: Return all Spells and Traps on the field to the hand.
②：The first time this card would be destroyed by battle each turn, it is not destroyed.

name: Magnetic Warior Magnet Tellusrion
desc:
Cannot be Normal Summoned/Set. 
Must be Special Summoned (from your GY) by banishing 1 "Magnet Warrior Σ+" and 1 "Magnet Warrior Σ-" from your hand, face-up field, and/or GY.
①：Once per turn, when your opponent activates a card or effect (Quick Effect): You can target 1 monster your opponent controls; destroy it, or, if it was an EARTH monster at activation, you can take control of it instead.
②：During your opponent's turn (Quick Effect): You can Tribute this card; Special Summon 2 of your banished "Magnet Warrior Σ" monsters.

name: Magnet Warrior Σ+
desc:
You can only use the ③ effect of this card's name once per turn.
①：All opponent's monsters must attack, if able, while you control an EARTH monster.
②：You choose the attack targets for your opponent's attacks while they control an EARTH monster.
③：If this card is sent to the GY: You can target 1 Level 4 or lower "Magnet Warrior" monster in your GY, except "Magnet Warrior Σ+"; add it to your hand or Special Summon it.

name: Magnet Warrior Σ-
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：You can reveal this card in your hand; Fusion Summon 1 Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck, using Rock monsters from your hand and/or field, including this card in your hand.
②：If this card is Normal or Special Summoned: You can send 1 Level 8 "Magna Warrior" monster from your Deck to your GY.
③：Once per turn, when an attack is declared between 2 EARTH monsters: You can negate that attack.

name: Vic Viper Type-L
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：At the start of your Battle Phase: You can activate 1 of these effects;
● Special Summon 1 Machine monster from your hand.
● Send 1 Level 4 or lower LIGHT Machine monster from your Deck to the GY.
②：If this card is destroyed: You can target 1 LIGHT Machine monster in your GY; Special Summon it, and if its original ATK is 1200 or less, it gains 1200 ATK.

name: B.E.S. Dellinger Core
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：You can reveal 1 other "B.E.S" monster in your hand; Special Summon this card from your hand, then place 3 counters on it.
②：During the Main Phase (Quick Effect): You can remove 1 counter from this card, then activate 1 of these effects;
● Add 1 "Boss Rush" or 1 Spell/Trap that mentions it from your Deck to your hand.
● Special Summon 1 Level 9 or lower "B.E.S." monster from your GY.

name: Super B.E.S. Metal Slave
desc:
You can only use the ① effect of this card's name once per turn.
①：You can send up to 5 Level 10 or lower "B.E.S." monsters with different names from your hand and/or Deck to the GY; Special Summon this card from your hand, then place counters on it equal to the number of cards sent to the GY to activate this effect.
②：Once per Chain (Quick Effect): You can remove 1 counter from this card, then target 2 face-up cards on the field, including a "B.E.S" monster you control; destroy them.

name: Tri-Brigade Springans Kitt
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：If you control a "Tri-Brigade" or "Springans" monster other than "Tri-Brigade Springans Kitt": You can Special Summon this card from your hand.
②：If this card is sent to the GY: You can Special Summon 1 of these from your GY, except "Tri-Brigade Springans Kitt".
● "Tri-Brigade" monster
● "Springans" monster
● "Fallen of Albaz" or a monster that mentions it

name: Conduction Knight Plasma Magnum
desc:
2 EARTH Rock monsters
You can only use the ① and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：If this card is Fusion Summoned: You can add 1 "Magnet" Normal, Quick-Play, or Field Spell from your Deck to your hand.
②：Monsters on the field become EARTH.
③：You can send 1 Level 8 "Magna Warrior" monster from your Deck to your GY; immediately after this effect resolves, Normal Summon 1 Level 4 or lower "Magnet Warrior" monster.

name: Gung-ho! Springans!
desc:
2+ Level 4 "Springans" monsters
You can only use 1 of the ① and ② effect of this card's name per turn, and only once that turn.
①：If this card is Xyz Summoned or sent to the GY: You can Special Summon 1 "Springans Captain Sargas" from your Deck or GY.
②：You can detach 2 materials from this card; add to your hand, or Special Summon, 1 of these from your Deck.
● "Springans" monster
● "Therion" monster
● "Fallen of Albaz" or a monster that mentions it

name: Topologic Blaster Dragon
desc:
2+ Effect Monsters
You cannot Summon/Set monsters to an Extra Monster Zone(s) this card points to.
①：If a monster(s) is Special Summoned to a zone(s) a Link Monster(s) points to while this card is in the Extra Monster Zone: Apply 1 of these effects, also you cannot apply that same effect of "Topologic Blaster Dragon" again for the rest of this turn.
● Shuffle all monsters on the field into the Deck, except this card.
● Shuffle all Spells and Traps on the field into the Deck.
● Look at your opponent's Extra Deck and banish 1 card from it.

name: Magnet Bonding
desc:
Quick-Play Spell Card
①：During the Main Phase: Activate 1 of these effects (but you can only use each effect of this card's name once per turn);
● Add 1 "Conduction Warrior Linear Magnum ±" or 1 Level 4 or lower "Magnet Warrior" monster from your Deck to your hand.
● Add 1 Level 8 "Magna Warrior" monster from your Deck to your hand.
● Fusion Summon 1 Rock Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck, by shuffling Rock monsters from your hand, field, GY, and/or banishment into the Deck.

name: Boss on Parade
desc:
You can only activate 1 card with this card's name per turn.
①：When this card resolves, add 1 "B.E.S." monster from your Deck to your hand.
②：Once per turn: You can destroy 1 monster in your hand or field, and if you do, Special Summon 1 LIGHT Machine monster with 1200 ATK and 1000 or less DEF from your Deck to either field.
③：You can banish this card from your GY; place 1 "Boss Rush" from your Deck or GY face-up on your field.

name: Arsenal Organization
desc:
You can only use 1 of the ① and ② effect of this card's name per turn, and only once that turn.
①：Send up to 2 Equip Spells with different names from your Deck to the GY.
②：You can banish this card from your GY, then target 1 face-up monster you control; equip up to 2 appropriate Equip Spells with different names from your hand and/or GY to it, but any battle damage it inflicts to your opponent is halved while equipped with either of them.

name: End of the World Ruler
desc:
You can Ritual Summon this card with any "End of the World" card. You can only use the ② and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：This card's name becomes "Demise, King of Armageddon" while in the hand or field.
②：You can reveal this card in your hand, pay 2000 LP, and banish 1 Ritual Spell from your Deck; apply that card's activation effect that Ritual Summons a monster.
③：You can pay 2000 LP; destroy as many other cards on the field as possible, then this card gains 2900 ATK.

name: Nightmare-Eyes Restrict
desc:
2 monsters with different Types (Fiend, Illusion, Spellcaster)
You can only use the ① effect of this card's name once per turn.
①：If this card is Special Summoned, OR, if this card battles, at the end of the Battle Phase: You can equip 1 monster your opponent controls to it.
②：Gains ATK equal to those equipped monsters' total ATK.
③：If this card battles a monster, neither can be destroyed by that battle.
④：Your opponent's monsters cannot attack monsters, except this one.

name: Zaren the Chainbound Dragon
desc:
1 Tuner + 1+ Synchro monsters
You can only use the ② effect of this card's name once per turn.
①：If this card you control would be used as Synchro Material, you can treat it as a non-Tuner.
②：When a card or effect is activated in response to the activation of a card or effect (Quick Effect): You can activate 1 of these effects;
● Negate that effect, and if you do, destroy that card.
● Negate the effects of the card that was responded to, and if you do, destroy it.

name: Nightmare Hand
desc:
You can only use 1 of the ① and ② effect of this card's name per turn, and only once that turn.
①：Send 1 Illusion monster from your Deck to the GY.
②：During your Main Phase, if you control a Level 5 or higher Illusion monster: You can banish this card from your GY, then target 1 monster in your opponent's GY; Special Summon it to your field, but banish it during the End Phase of the next turn.

name: Riot
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effects of this card's name each once per turn.
①：Target 1 Set monster; return it to the hand, then the player who added it to their hand can Special Summon 1 monster from their hand in face-down Defense Position.
②：When an opponent's monster declares an attack: You can banish this card from your GY; change 1 Set monster to Attack Position.

name: Dragunity Quirinus
desc:
You can only use the ① and ③ effects of this card's name each once per turn.
①：If this card is Normal or Special Summoned: You can add 1 "Dragunity" Spell/Trap from your Deck to your hand.
②：Your "Dragunity" monsters cannot be destroyed by battle while this card is equipped with an Equip Card.
③：You can target 1 other "Dragunity" Monster Card you control; return it to the hand/Extra Deck, then you can Special Summon 1 "Dragunity" monster from your hand.

name: Dragunity Falchion
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：You can banish this card from your hand or GY, then target 1 "Dragunity" monster you control; equip 1 Dragon "Dragunity" monster from your Deck or GY to it.
②：You can send this card equipped to a "Dragunity" monster to the GY, then target 1 face-up card your opponent controls; banish it.

name: Dragunity Knight – Areus
desc:
1 Tuner + 1+ non-Tuner Synchro Monsters
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：You can target face-up cards your opponent controls up to the number of face-up Monster Cards in your Spell & Trap Zone; negate their effects until the end of this turn. This is a Quick Effect if this card is equipped with an Equip Card.
③：While this card is equipped to a monster: You can Special Summon it, then you can Special Summon 1 "Dragunity" Tuner from your GY.

name: Dragunity Lord – Georgius
desc:
2+ monsters, including a Tuner
You can only use the ① and ③ effect of this card's name once per turn.
①：If this card is Link Summoned, or your opponent Special Summons a monster(s): You can Special Summon 1 Level 5 or higher "Dragunity" monster from your Extra Deck or GY.
②：Your opponent cannot activate monster effects in the GY while this card is equipped with a "Dragunity" card.
③：When your opponent activates a Spell/Trap Card or effect (Quick Effect): You can send 1 Equip Card you control to the GY; negate that effect.

name: Elvennotes Lucina
desc:
You can only Special Summon with the ① effect of this card's name once per turn. You can only use the ② and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：You can Special Summon this card (from your hand) to your center Main Monster Zone.
②：During your Main Phase: You can add 1 "Elvennotes" monster from your Deck to your hand, except "Elvennotes Lucina".
③：During your opponent's turn (Quick Effect): You can switch the locations of this card you control and the monster in your center Main Monster Zone, then you can return 1 Level 6 or lower monster your opponent controls to the hand.

name: Elvennotes Dyina
desc:
You can only Special Summon with the ① effect of this card's name once per turn. You can only use the ② and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：You can Special Summon this card (from your hand) to your center Main Monster Zone.
②：During your Main Phase: You can place 1 "Elvennotes" Continuous Spell from your Deck on your field face-up.
③：During your opponent's turn (Quick Effect): You can switch the locations of this card you control and the monster in your center Main Monster Zone, then you can banish 1 random card from your opponent's hand face-up until the End Phase.

name: Elvennotes Fortona
desc:
You can only Special Summon with the ① effect of this card's name once per turn. You can only use the ② and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：You can Special Summon this card (from your hand) to your center Main Monster Zone.
②：During your Main Phase: You can place 1 "Elvennotes" Continuous Trap from your hand or Deck on your field face-up.
③：During your opponent's turn (Quick Effect): You can switch the locations of this card you control and the monster in your center Main Monster Zone, then you can return 1 face-up Spell/Trap on the field to the hand.

name: Elvennotes Power Patron
desc:
You can only use the ② and ③ effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：You cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck, except Synchro Monsters.
②：During the Main Phase (Quick Effect): You can target the monster in your center Main Monster Zone; increase its Level by 3 (until the end of this turn), then, immediately after this effect resolves, you can Synchro Summon 1 "Elvennotes" monster or "Junora the Power Patron of Tuning".
③：If this card is sent to the GY as Synchro Material: You can add 1 "Elvennotes" card from your Deck to your hand.

name: Junora the Power Patron of Tuning
desc:
1 Tuner + 2 non-Tuner monsters
For this card's Synchro Summon, you can treat a monster in your center Main Monster Zone as a Tuner. You can only use the ② effect of this card's name once per turn.
①：If this card is Synchro Summoned: You can negate the effects of all face-up cards your opponent currently controls.
②：(Quick Efect): You can make all opponent's monsters in the same columns as your "Elvennotes" monsters unable to be used as material for a Fusion, Synchro, Xyz, or Link Summon until the end of this turn

name: Elvennotes Seraphim Stlitzia
desc:
1 Tuner + 1+ non-Tuner monsters
You can only use the ② effect of this card's name once per turn.
①：This card's original ATK becomes 3000 while in the center Main Monster Zone.
②：During the Main Phase (Quick Effect): You can Special Summon 1 Level 6 or lower "Elvennotes" monster from your hand or GY, then you can decrease the Levels of all Level 4 or higher monsters currently on the field by 3 until the end of this turn, also you cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn, except Synchro Monsters.

name: DoomZ Changer
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：Destroy 1 "DoomZ" card in your hand, Deck, or face-up field, except "DoomZ Changer".
②：If this card is destroyed by card effect: You can add 1 "DoomZ" card from your GY to your hand, except "DoomZ Changer", then you can Special Summon 1 "DoomZ" monster from your hand.

name: Elvennotes ~Homecoming Paralleism~
desc:
You can only use the ② effect of this card's name once per turn.
①：A monster in your center Main Monster Zone cannot be destroyed by card effects.
②：You can send 1 monster from your hand or field to the GY; Special Summon 1 "Elvennotes" monster with a different original Attribute from your Deck in Defense Position, also you cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn, except Synchro Monsters.

name: Elvennotes ~Reunion Tercet~
desc:
①：Your opponent cannot target a monster in your center Main Monster Zone with card effects.
②：This card gains these effects based on the Attribute(s) of the monster in your center Main Monster Zone.
● FIRE/EARTH: If your Synchro Monster attacks a Defense Position monster, inflict piercing battle damage.
● WATER/WIND: Other face-up Spells/Traps you control cannot be destroyed by your opponent's card effects.
● LIGHT/DARK: You take no battle damage.

name: Theorealize Liberation
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effect of this card's name each once per turn.
①：If you control "Medius the Pure": Add to your hand, or Special Summon, 1 monster from your Deck with 300 ATK/200 DEF.
②：During your Main Phase: You can banish this card from your GY, then target 1 face-up monster you control; it is treated as a Tuner this turn.

name: Elvennotes ~Oracle Alicetea~
desc:
You can only use the ② effect of this card's name once per turn. You cannot activate the ① and ② effect of this card's name in the same Chain.
①：Once per turn: You can target 1 face-up monster you control; move that monster you control to another of your Main Monster Zones.
②：When your opponent activates a Spell/Trap Card, if you control 3 or more "Elvennotes" monsters: You can negate that effect, then, if you control a Synchro Monster, you can destroy that card.

name: Elvennotes ~Maddening Rhapsodia~
desc:
①：Your opponent's monsters cannot attack while you have a monster in your center Main Monster Zone, except to attack it.
②：You can send 1 monster from your hand or field to the GY, then target 1 "Elvennotes" monster in your GY with a different original Attribute; Special Summon it, then, if you control a Synchro Monster, you can negate the effects of 1 face-up card your opponent controls until the end of this turn.

name: Junk Warrior/Assault Mode
desc:
Cannot be Normal Summoned/Set. Must be Special Summoned with "Assault Mode Activate".
①：Gains 1000 ATK for each "/Assault Mode" monster you control. If this card battles a monster, any battle damage it inflicts to your opponent is doubled.
②：Unaffected by your opponent's activated monster effects.
③：If this card is destroyed: You can target 1 "Junk Warrior" in your GY; return it to the Extra Deck, then Special Summon it (this is treated as a Synchro Summon).

name: Crimson Blader/Assault Mode
desc:
Cannot be Normal Summoned/Set. Must be Special Summoned with "Assault Mode Activate". You can only use the ① effect of this card's name once per turn.
①：You can reveal this card in your hand; add 1 "Assault Mode Activate", or 1 card that mentions it, from your Deck to your hand, then shuffle this card into the Deck.
②：Your opponent cannot activate the effects of Level 5 or higher monsters Special Summoned from the Extra Deck.
③：If this card is destroyed: You can Special Summon 1 "Crimson Blader" from your GY.

name: Assault Lich
desc:
You can only use the ① and ③ effects of this card's name once per turn.
①：If this card is Normal or Special Summoned: You can Special Summon 1 monster that mentions "Assault Mode Activate" or 1 Level 4 or lower Zombie monster from your GY.
②：If this card you control would be used as Synchro Material, you can treat it as a non-Tuner.
③：If this card is sent to the GY as Synchro Material: You can add 1 "Assault Slash" or "Assault Counter" from your Deck to your hand.

name: Night Wing Priestess
desc:
You can only use the ① and ② effects of this card's name once per turn.
①：If this card is Special Summoned: You can Set 1 "Assault Mode Activate" from your hand, Deck, or GY. It can be activated this turn.
②：You can discard 1 card; add to your hand, or Special Summon, 1 monster from your Deck that mentions "Assault Mode Activate", also you cannot Special Summon from the Extra Deck for the rest of this turn, except Synchro Monsters.

name: Duel Evolution – Assault Zone
desc:
You can only activate 1 card with this card's name per turn. You can only use the ③ effect of this card's name once per turn.
